  "ai_lead_paragraph": "This week produced 12 pathogen-related recall incidents across the AFTS monitoring network — a substantial contraction from W15's 63-incident spike, with the pathogen profile rebalancing to a more typical distribution: 5 Listeria monocytogenes and 5 Salmonella spp. incidents with 7 Tier-1 classifications overall. Two distinct Clostridium botulinum recalls this week — Liquid Blenz Corp (US, Good Brain Tonic) and Marché Rio (Canada, Haitian spices) — warrant elevated operator attention; both involve low-acid products where incomplete thermal processing or undefined water-activity control can permit toxin formation. The ongoing Canadian multi-serotype Salmonella pistachio outbreak (189 confirmed cases, 26 hospitalizations across six provinces per PHAC) expanded this week with Sultan Fine Foods and chocoStyle 440 recalls, indicating supplier-side contamination has not been contained at source.",
